</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,1347]" box="[151,1436,181,203]" pageId="6" pageNumber="157">
<keyLead box="[151,1436,181,203]" pageId="6" pageNumber="157">- Elytra without robust tubercles in interstriae 2, 3, and 5, only granules of lesser degrees of development................ 3</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="6" pageNumber="157">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,1347]" pageId="6" pageNumber="157">
<keyLead pageId="6" pageNumber="157">3 Posterior femur not exceeding abdominal ventrite 3, or rarely reaching at most abdominal ventrite 4; elytra with macula occupying the posterior slope of the elytra................................................................... 4</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,1347]" box="[151,1436,269,291]" pageId="6" pageNumber="157">
<keyLead box="[151,1436,269,291]" pageId="6" pageNumber="157">- Posterior femur exceeding abdominal ventrite 3; elytra with or without macula in different positions................... 5</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="6" pageNumber="157">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,1347]" pageId="6" pageNumber="157">
<keyLead pageId="6" pageNumber="157">
4 Elytra with protuberant, umbilicate granules, each with an extremely short (sometimes indistinct) scale (
<figureCitation box="[1227,1297,298,320]" captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="27.[151,250,2012,2036]" captionTargetBox="[160,1428,1273,1978]" captionTargetId="figure-413@27.[151,1435,1265,1988]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 17. Syntype Heilus bistigma. A. dorsal view. B. lateral view. C. labels. The copyright of images belongs to MNHN." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4414720" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4414720/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="157">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
