<bibRefCitation author="Hustache, A." box="[1271,1429,327,349]" pageId="6" pageNumber="157" pagination="334 - 349" refId="ref28896" refString="Hustache, A. (1938) Curculionides nouveaux de l'Amerique meridionale, qui se trouvent dans le Deutsches Entomologisches Institut. 3 eme note. Arbeiten uber morphologische und taxonomische Entomologie aus Berlin-Dahlen, 5 (4), 334 - 349." type="journal article" year="1938">Hustache, 1938</bibRefCitation>
)
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,1347]" pageId="6" pageNumber="157">
<keyLead pageId="6" pageNumber="157">
- Elytra with non-protuberant and non-umbilicate granules, each one with a short and distinct scale at the apex (
<figureCitation box="[1283,1341,357,379]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="15.[151,250,978,1002]" captionTargetBox="[160,1424,247,948]" captionTargetId="figure-40@15.[151,1436,237,954]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 7. Holotype Heilus rufescens, female. A. dorsal view. B. lateral view. C. labels. The copyright of images belongs to NHRS." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4414700" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4414700/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="157">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
)................................................................................ 
