<emphasis bold="true" box="[1158,1285,533,554]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="157">H. inornatus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Kirsch, T." box="[1297,1429,532,554]" pageId="6" pageNumber="157" pagination="385 - 432" refId="ref29004" refString="Kirsch, T. (1874) Beitrage zur Kenntnis der Peruanischen Kaferfauna auf Dr. Abendroth's Sammlungen basirt. Berliner entomologische Zeitschrift, 18, 385 - 432. https: // doi. org / 10.1002 / mmnd. 18740180324" type="journal article" year="1874">Kirsch, 1874</bibRefCitation>
)
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,1347]" pageId="6" pageNumber="157">
<keyLead pageId="6" pageNumber="157">
- Pronotum more strongly rounded on the sides, 1.3 times wider than long; with dense yellow scales forming a transverse band at the base of elytra and another one in the posterior third interrupted at the striae (
<figureCitation box="[1017,1086,591,613]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="25.[151,250,1973,1997]" captionTargetBox="[160,1424,1323,1945]" captionTargetId="figure-508@25.[151,1435,1317,1950]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURE 15. Holotype Heilus iniquus, undetermined sex. A. dorsal view. B. lateral view. C. labels. The copyright of images belongs to SGND." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4414716" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4414716/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="157">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
)..... 
<taxonomicName authority="(Kirsch, 1874)" authorityName="Kuschel" baseAuthorityName="Kirsch" baseAuthorityYear="1874" box="[1180,1436,591,613]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Heilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="157" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="iniquus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1180,1428,591,613]" pageId="6" pageNumber="157">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1180,1285,591,613]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="157">H. iniquus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Kirsch, T." box="[1297,1428,591,613]" pageId="6" pageNumber="157" pagination="385 - 432" refId="ref29004" refString="Kirsch, T. (1874) Beitrage zur Kenntnis der Peruanischen Kaferfauna auf Dr. Abendroth's Sammlungen basirt. Berliner entomologische Zeitschrift, 18, 385 - 432. https: // doi. org / 10.1002 / mmnd. 18740180324" type="journal article" year="1874">Kirsch, 1874</bibRefCitation>
</emphasis>
)
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="6" pageNumber="157">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,1347]" pageId="6" pageNumber="157">
<keyLead pageId="6" pageNumber="157">7 Elytra without granules throughout length of interstria 1, rarely with traces of tiny granules in the apical third; with elytral macula............................................................................................. 8</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,1347]" pageId="6" pageNumber="157">
<keyLead pageId="6" pageNumber="157">- Elytra with small and obsolete granules, starting from midlength of interstria 1 to the apex, or only a few tiny granules near the apex; with or without macula on the elytra................................................................. 9</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="6" pageNumber="157">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,1347]" pageId="6" pageNumber="157">
<keyLead pageId="6" pageNumber="157">
