<emphasis bold="true" box="[1124,1437,796,818]" pageId="6" pageNumber="157">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1124,1257,796,818]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="157">H. inaequalis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Boheman, C. H." box="[1269,1429,796,818]" pageId="6" pageNumber="157" pagination="1836" refId="ref28117" refString="Boheman, C. H. (1836) In: Schonherr, C. J. (1836), q. v." type="book chapter" year="1836">Boheman, 1836</bibRefCitation>
)
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,1347]" pageId="6" pageNumber="157">
<keyLead pageId="6" pageNumber="157">
- Pronotum and elytra with smaller, sparse granules; elytra with larger, rounded macula, usually occupying interstriae 3 to 6 or 7, entirely outlined by a narrow band of whitish scales (
<figureCitation box="[736,794,855,878]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="18.[151,250,1124,1148]" captionTargetBox="[160,1428,459,1093]" captionTargetId="figure-130@18.[151,1437,453,1101]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 9. Holotype Heilus myops, female. A. dorsal view. B. lateral view. C. labels. The copyright of images belongs to NHRS." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4414704" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4414704/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="157">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
)............................. 
